{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":714,"text":"Back in 2003,"},{"time":3834,"text":"the UK government carried out a survey."},{"time":7494,"text":"And it was a survey that measured\nlevels of numeracy"},{"time":10667,"text":"in the population."},{"time":11928,"text":"And they were shocked to find out"},{"time":13595,"text":"that for every 100 working age\nadults in the country,"},{"time":16983,"text":"47 of them lacked Level 1 numeracy skills."},{"time":20892,"text":"Now, Level 1 numeracy skills --\nthat's low-end GCSE score."},{"time":25410,"text":"It's the ability to deal with fractions,\npercentages and decimals."},{"time":28682,"text":"So this figure prompted\na lot of hand-wringing in Whitehall."},{"time":33334,"text":"Policies were changed,"},{"time":34986,"text":"investments were made,"},{"time":36732,"text":"and then they ran\nthe survey again in 2011."},{"time":39794,"text":"So can you guess\nwhat happened to this number?"},{"time":44021,"text":"It went up to 49."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45489,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":46962,"text":"And in fact, when I reported\nthis figure in the FT,"},{"time":49435,"text":"one of our readers joked and said,"},{"time":51130,"text":"\"This figure is only shocking\nto 51 percent of the population.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":54915,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":57225,"text":"But I preferred, actually,\nthe reaction of a schoolchild"},{"time":60406,"text":"when I presented\nat a school this information,"},{"time":63525,"text":"who raised their hand and said,"},{"time":65080,"text":"\"How do we know that the person\nwho made that number"},{"time":67620,"text":"isn't one of the 49 percent either?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":69459,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":70737,"text":"So clearly, there's a numeracy issue,"},{"time":74811,"text":"because these are\nimportant skills for life,"},{"time":76945,"text":"and a lot of the changes\nthat we want to introduce in this century"},{"time":80836,"text":"involve us becoming\nmore comfortable with numbers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83301,"text":"Now, it's not just an English problem."},{"time":85173,"text":"OECD this year released some figures\nlooking at numeracy in young people,"},{"time":90127,"text":"and leading the way, the USA --"},{"time":92931,"text":"nearly 40 percent of young people\nin the US have low numeracy."},{"time":97625,"text":"Now, England is there too,"},{"time":98946,"text":"but there are seven OECD countries\nwith figures above 20 percent."},{"time":104503,"text":"That is a problem,\nbecause it doesn't have to be that way."},{"time":107286,"text":"If you look at the far end of this graph,"},{"time":109318,"text":"you can see the Netherlands and Korea\nare in single figures."},{"time":112302,"text":"So there's definitely a numeracy\nproblem that we want to address."}]},{"cues":[{"time":117510,"text":"Now, as useful as studies like these are,"},{"time":120464,"text":"I think we risk herding people\ninadvertently into one of two categories;"},{"time":125888,"text":"that there are two kinds of people:"},{"time":127688,"text":"those people that are comfortable\nwith numbers, that can do numbers,"},{"time":132061,"text":"and the people who can't."},{"time":134321,"text":"And what I'm trying\nto talk about here today"},{"time":136446,"text":"is to say that I believe\nthat is a false dichotomy."},{"time":139512,"text":"It's not an immutable pairing."},{"time":141404,"text":"I think you don't have to have\ntremendously high levels of numeracy"},{"time":145076,"text":"to be inspired by numbers,"},{"time":146828,"text":"and that should be the starting point\nto the journey ahead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":150387,"text":"And one of the ways in which\nwe can begin that journey, for me,"},{"time":154722,"text":"is looking at statistics."},{"time":156472,"text":"Now, I am the first to acknowledge\nthat statistics has got somewhat"},{"time":159991,"text":"of an image problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161333,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":162404,"text":"It's the part of mathematics"},{"time":163960,"text":"that even mathematicians\ndon't particularly like,"},{"time":167043,"text":"because whereas the rest of maths\nis all about precision and certainty,"},{"time":171079,"text":"statistics is almost the reverse of that."},{"time":173793,"text":"But actually, I was a late convert\nto the world of statistics myself."},{"time":178472,"text":"If you'd asked my undergraduate professors"},{"time":180578,"text":"what two subjects would I be least likely\nto excel in after university,"},{"time":185361,"text":"they'd have told you statistics\nand computer programming,"},{"time":188152,"text":"and yet here I am, about to show you\nsome statistical graphics"},{"time":191115,"text":"that I programmed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192745,"text":"So what inspired that change in me?"},{"time":194524,"text":"What made me think that statistics\nwas actually an interesting thing?"},{"time":198196,"text":"It's really because\nstatistics are about us."},{"time":200869,"text":"If you look at the etymology\nof the word statistics,"},{"time":203475,"text":"it's the science of dealing with data"},{"time":206108,"text":"about the state or the community\nthat we live in."},{"time":208562,"text":"So statistics are about us as a group,"},{"time":211940,"text":"not us as individuals."},{"time":213639,"text":"And I think as social animals,"},{"time":215133,"text":"we share this fascination about how\nwe as individuals relate to our groups,"},{"time":219101,"text":"to our peers."},{"time":220513,"text":"And statistics in this way\nare at their most powerful"},{"time":223647,"text":"when they surprise us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":225477,"text":"And there's been some really wonderful\nsurveys carried out recently"},{"time":228708,"text":"by Ipsos MORI in the last few years."},{"time":230446,"text":"They did a survey of over\n1,000 adults in the UK,"},{"time":233178,"text":"and said, for every 100 people\nin England and Wales,"},{"time":236982,"text":"how many of them are Muslim?"},{"time":238876,"text":"Now the average answer from this survey,"},{"time":241546,"text":"which was supposed to be representative\nof the total population, was 24."},{"time":244982,"text":"That's what people thought."},{"time":248682,"text":"British people think 24 out of every 100\npeople in the country are Muslim."},{"time":252345,"text":"Now, official figures reveal\nthat figure to be about five."},{"time":257732,"text":"So there's this big variation\nbetween what we think, our perception,"},{"time":261743,"text":"and the reality as given by statistics."},{"time":263805,"text":"And I think that's interesting."},{"time":265373,"text":"What could possibly be causing\nthat misperception?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":269212,"text":"And I was so thrilled with this study,"},{"time":271090,"text":"I started to take questions out\nin presentations. I was referring to it."},{"time":274594,"text":"Now, I did a presentation"},{"time":275836,"text":"at St. Paul's School for Girls\nin Hammersmith,"},{"time":278170,"text":"and I had an audience rather like this,"},{"time":280334,"text":"except it was comprised entirely\nof sixth-form girls."},{"time":284226,"text":"And I said, \"Girls,"},{"time":287598,"text":"how many teenage girls do you think\nthe British public think"},{"time":292165,"text":"get pregnant every year?\""},{"time":293937,"text":"And the girls were apoplectic when I said"},{"time":297453,"text":"the British public think that 15\nout of every 100 teenage girls"},{"time":301390,"text":"get pregnant in the year."},{"time":303429,"text":"And they had every right to be angry,"},{"time":305684,"text":"because in fact, I'd have to have\ncloser to 200 dots"},{"time":308466,"text":"before I could color one in,"},{"time":310060,"text":"in terms of what\nthe official figures tell us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312599,"text":"And rather like numeracy,\nthis is not just an English problem."},{"time":316423,"text":"Ipsos MORI expanded the survey\nin recent years to go across the world."},{"time":320951,"text":"And so, they asked Saudi Arabians,"},{"time":323925,"text":"for every 100 adults in your country,"},{"time":326470,"text":"how many of them are overweight or obese?"},{"time":330526,"text":"And the average answer from the Saudis\nwas just over a quarter."},{"time":336402,"text":"That's what they thought."},{"time":337628,"text":"Just over a quarter of adults\nare overweight or obese."},{"time":340220,"text":"The official figures show, actually,\nit's nearer to three-quarters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":345025,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":346505,"text":"So again, a big variation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348821,"text":"And I love this one: they asked in Japan,\nthey asked the Japanese,"},{"time":353291,"text":"for every 100 Japanese people,"},{"time":355275,"text":"how many of them live in rural areas?"},{"time":358521,"text":"The average was about a 50-50 split,\njust over halfway."},{"time":363446,"text":"They thought 56 out of every 100\nJapanese people lived in rural areas."},{"time":367617,"text":"The official figure is seven."}]},{"cues":[{"time":370259,"text":"So extraordinary variations,\nand surprising to some,"},{"time":374733,"text":"but not surprising to people\nwho have read the work"},{"time":377146,"text":"of Daniel Kahneman, for example,\nthe Nobel-winning economist."},{"time":381562,"text":"He and his colleague, Amos Tversky,\nspent years researching this disjoint"},{"time":386678,"text":"between what people perceive\nand the reality,"},{"time":389847,"text":"the fact that people are actually\npretty poor intuitive statisticians."},{"time":393622,"text":"And there are many reasons for this."},{"time":395406,"text":"Individual experiences, certainly,\ncan influence our perceptions,"},{"time":398545,"text":"but so, too, can things like the media\nreporting things by exception,"},{"time":402527,"text":"rather than what's normal."},{"time":404855,"text":"Kahneman had a nice way\nof referring to that."},{"time":407005,"text":"He said, \"We can be blind\nto the obvious\" --"},{"time":409114,"text":"so we've got the numbers wrong --"},{"time":410776,"text":"\"but we can be blind\nto our blindness about it.\""},{"time":413122,"text":"And that has enormous\nrepercussions for decision making."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416412,"text":"So at the statistics office\nwhile this was all going on,"},{"time":419288,"text":"I thought this was really interesting."},{"time":421224,"text":"I said, this is clearly a global problem,"},{"time":423258,"text":"but maybe geography is the issue here."},{"time":425717,"text":"These were questions that were all about,\nhow well do you know your country?"},{"time":429650,"text":"So in this case, it's how well\ndo you know 64 million people?"},{"time":433667,"text":"Not very well, it turns out.\nI can't do that."},{"time":436423,"text":"So I had an idea,"},{"time":437771,"text":"which was to think about\nthis same sort of approach"},{"time":440918,"text":"but to think about it\nin a very local sense."},{"time":443047,"text":"Is this a local?"},{"time":444262,"text":"If we reframe the questions and say,"},{"time":446227,"text":"how well do you know your local area,"},{"time":448373,"text":"would your answers be any more accurate?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":451817,"text":"So I devised a quiz:"},{"time":453603,"text":"How well do you know your area?"},{"time":456454,"text":"It's a simple Web app."},{"time":458367,"text":"You put in a post code"},{"time":459574,"text":"and then it will ask you questions\nbased on census data"},{"time":462305,"text":"for your local area."},{"time":464305,"text":"And I was very conscious\nin designing this."},{"time":466452,"text":"I wanted to make it open\nto the widest possible range of people,"},{"time":470585,"text":"not just the 49 percent\nwho can get the numbers."},{"time":473437,"text":"I wanted everyone to engage with it."},{"time":475216,"text":"So for the design of the quiz,"},{"time":476765,"text":"I was inspired by the isotypes"},{"time":480404,"text":"of Otto Neurath from the 1920s and '30s."},{"time":483030,"text":"Now, these are methods\nfor representing numbers"},{"time":487402,"text":"using repeating icons."},{"time":489640,"text":"And the numbers are there,\nbut they sit in the background."},{"time":492829,"text":"So it's a great way\nof representing quantity"},{"time":495576,"text":"without resorting to using terms\nlike \"percentage,\""},{"time":498584,"text":"\"fractions\" and \"ratios.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":499838,"text":"So here's the quiz."},{"time":502310,"text":"The layout of the quiz is,"},{"time":503981,"text":"you have your repeating icons\non the left-hand side there,"},{"time":506824,"text":"and a map showing you the area\nwe're asking you questions about"},{"time":509971,"text":"on the right-hand side."},{"time":511162,"text":"There are seven questions."},{"time":512467,"text":"Each question, there's a possible answer\nbetween zero and a hundred,"},{"time":516384,"text":"and at the end of the quiz,"},{"time":517757,"text":"you get an overall score\nbetween zero and a hundred."},{"time":520999,"text":"And so because this is TEDxExeter,"},{"time":523107,"text":"I thought we would have\na quick look at the quiz"},{"time":525456,"text":"for the first few questions of Exeter."},{"time":527789,"text":"And so the first question is:"},{"time":529218,"text":"For every 100 people,\nhow many are aged under 16?"},{"time":532784,"text":"Now, I don't know Exeter very well\nat all, so I had a guess at this,"},{"time":536408,"text":"but it gives you an idea\nof how this quiz works."},{"time":538993,"text":"You drag the slider\nto highlight your icons,"},{"time":542723,"text":"and then just click \"Submit\" to answer,"},{"time":544982,"text":"and we animate away the difference\nbetween your answer and reality."},{"time":548669,"text":"And it turns out, I was a pretty\nterrible guess: five."}]},{"cues":[{"time":553149,"text":"How about the next question?"},{"time":554597,"text":"This is asking about\nwhat the average age is,"},{"time":556777,"text":"so the age at which half\nthe population are younger"},{"time":559246,"text":"and half the population are older."},{"time":560944,"text":"And I thought 35 -- that sounds\nmiddle-aged to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":564318,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":568206,"text":"Actually, in Exeter,\nit's incredibly young,"},{"time":570336,"text":"and I had underestimated the impact\nof the university in this area."},{"time":574898,"text":"The questions get harder\nas you go through."},{"time":576953,"text":"So this one's now asking\nabout homeownership:"},{"time":579955,"text":"For every 100 households, how many\nare owned with a mortgage or loan?"},{"time":583678,"text":"And I hedged my bets here,"},{"time":584982,"text":"because I didn't want to be\nmore than 50 out on the answer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588104,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":590148,"text":"And actually, these get harder,\nthese questions,"},{"time":592638,"text":"because when you're in an area,\nwhen you're in a community,"},{"time":595521,"text":"things like age -- there are clues\nto whether a population is old or young."},{"time":600795,"text":"Just by looking around\nthe area, you can see it."},{"time":603164,"text":"Something like homeownership\nis much more difficult to see,"},{"time":606579,"text":"so we revert to our own heuristics,"},{"time":609211,"text":"our own biases about how many people\nwe think own their own homes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":613686,"text":"Now the truth is,\nwhen we published this quiz,"},{"time":617360,"text":"the census data that it's based on\nwas already a few years old."},{"time":620920,"text":"We've had online applications\nthat allow you to put in a post code"},{"time":624513,"text":"and get statistics back for years."},{"time":626631,"text":"So in some senses,"},{"time":627844,"text":"this was all a little bit old\nand not necessarily new."},{"time":631417,"text":"But I was interested to see\nwhat reaction we might get"},{"time":635080,"text":"by gamifying the data\nin the way that we have,"},{"time":637821,"text":"by using animation"},{"time":639252,"text":"and playing on the fact\nthat people have their own preconceptions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":643508,"text":"It turns out, the reaction was, um ..."},{"time":648328,"text":"was more than I could have hoped for."},{"time":650280,"text":"It was a long-held ambition of mine\nto bring down a statistics website"},{"time":653685,"text":"due to public demand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":655117,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":656941,"text":"This URL contains the words\n\"statistics,\" \"gov\" and \"UK,\""},{"time":660429,"text":"which are three of people's least\nfavorite words in a URL."},{"time":663695,"text":"And the amazing thing about this\nwas that the website came down"},{"time":667704,"text":"at quarter to 10 at night,"},{"time":669821,"text":"because people were actually\nengaging with this data"},{"time":673056,"text":"of their own free will,"},{"time":674619,"text":"using their own personal time."},{"time":676678,"text":"I was very interested to see"},{"time":679189,"text":"that we got something like\na quarter of a million people"},{"time":682926,"text":"playing the quiz within the space\nof 48 hours of launching it."},{"time":686222,"text":"And it sparked an enormous discussion\nonline, on social media,"},{"time":690173,"text":"which was largely dominated"},{"time":692234,"text":"by people having fun\nwith their misconceptions,"},{"time":696251,"text":"which is something that\nI couldn't have hoped for any better,"},{"time":699334,"text":"in some respects."},{"time":700518,"text":"I also liked the fact that people started\nsending it to politicians."},{"time":703768,"text":"How well do you know the area\nyou claim to represent?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":706381,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":707567,"text":"And then just to finish,"},{"time":709992,"text":"going back to the two kinds of people,"},{"time":712346,"text":"I thought it would be\nreally interesting to see"},{"time":714627,"text":"how people who are good with numbers\nwould do on this quiz."},{"time":717466,"text":"The national statistician\nof England and Wales, John Pullinger,"},{"time":720506,"text":"you would expect he would be pretty good."},{"time":723524,"text":"He got 44 for his own area."}]},{"cues":[{"time":725997,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":728489,"text":"Jeremy Paxman -- admittedly,\nafter a glass of wine -- 36."},{"time":734051,"text":"Even worse."},{"time":735536,"text":"It just shows you that the numbers\ncan inspire us all."},{"time":738761,"text":"They can surprise us all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":740045,"text":"So very often, we talk about statistics"},{"time":742108,"text":"as being the science of uncertainty."},{"time":744094,"text":"My parting thought for today is:"},{"time":745900,"text":"actually, statistics is the science of us."},{"time":748959,"text":"And that's why we should\nbe fascinated by numbers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":751771,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752985,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}